text.section:
"Clean-burning fuel" means, when used for motor vehicle propulsion:
natural gas;
liquefied natural gas;
liquefied petroleum gas;
hydrogen;
electricity; or
any other fuel at least 85% of which is one or more of the following:
methanol;
ethanol;
any other alcohol; or
ether.

section.section:
"Gasoline" includes:
casinghead gasoline;
absorption gasoline;
other natural gasoline; and
aviation gasoline.
